oai_dc:dc.dc:title: Post-Convention Proceedings of the Twenty-Fifth Annual Conference. New Directors and AABP Honorees
oai_dc:dc.dc:creator: Bovine Practitioners, American Association of
oai_dc:dc.dc:description: Dr. Delbert G. Miles, Greeley, Colorado is the new Director for District 9. Dr. Michael J. Anderson, Lynden, Washington, is the new Director, District 11. Dr. N. Kent Ames, East Lansing, Michigan is the new Director for District 4. Dr. Robert H. Keith, Monroe, Wisconsin, was presented the Stange Award at the Iowa State University Alumni Association Annual Honors and Awards Banquet at Ames, Iowa on June 6, 1992. Dr. Arnold F. Hentschl, Harbor Beach, Michigan was the recipient of the A VMA Award at this year's annual convention in Boston, MA. Dr. Leland C. Allenstein, Whitewater, Wisconsin, was selected 1992 Industry Person of the Year by World Dairy Expo.
